## Notes on C++ FFI Integration

- Rust creates and owns C++ object via opaque handle
- C++ gRPC server runs on its own thread pool
- Memory copying through FFI (buffers allocated in Rust, filled by C++)
- Rust `Drop` trait calls `fake_data_rw_destroy()` for cleanup

**Why FFI over pure Rust port**:
- Reuses battle-tested encryption/decryption logic from FCP
- Avoids duplicating complex HPKE + MessageEncryptor/MessageDecryptor code
- Maintains compatibility with existing proto definitions

